org.forgerock.openidm.sync.impl

Class LazyObjectAccessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.forgerock.openidm.sync.impl.LazyObjectAccessor

  • public class LazyObjectAccessor
extends Object
    Loads and caches the object only once on demand. This class is not thread safe.

      • rawReadObject

        public static org.forgerock.json.fluent.JsonValue rawReadObject(org.forgerock.json.resource.ServerContext router,
                                                org.forgerock.json.resource.ConnectionFactory connectionFactory,
                                                String resourceContainer,
                                                String resourceId)
                                                         throws SynchronizationException
        Tries to retrieve the object directly from where it is stored. Does not take into account any cached/lazy loaded object in this class. Typically access to objects should be through getObject() instead, which can support the lazy/cached loading.
        Parameters:
        resourceContainer - location where the object is stored
        resourceId - the object identifier
        Returns:
        the object value if found, null if not found
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if targetId is null.
        SynchronizationException - if retrieving the object failed
